  "routeEn": "The Behobia - San Sebastián route starts from the international bridge at Behobia, on the French border, and heads toward San Sebastián along the N-1 road and parallel paths. The first kilometers are slightly downhill following the Bidasoa valley. Around kilometer 6 begins the most demanding climb of the course, at Gaintxurizketa, with gradients reaching 6-8%. After the summit, the route descends toward the coast and the final kilometers run with views of the Cantabrian Sea before the final descent to the Boulevard in Donostia and the finish line near La Concha beach. Total positive elevation gain is around 200 meters. Aid stations are plentiful, approximately every 2.5 kilometers.",
